<reference id="api_irtcengineex_getuserinfobyuidex">
    <title><ph keyref="getUserInfoByUidEx"/></title>
    <shortdesc id="short"><ph id="shortdesc" props="cpp">Retrieves user information by user ID.</ph><ph id="shortdesc" props="android">Gets the user information by user ID.</ph></shortdesc>
    <prolog>
        <metadata>
            <keywords>
                <indexterm keyref="getUserInfoByUidEx"/>
            </keywords>
        </metadata>
    </prolog>
    <refbody>
        <section id="prototype">
            <p outputclass="codeblock">
                <codeblock props="cpp" outputclass="language-cpp">virtual int getUserInfoByUidEx(uid_t uid, rtc::UserInfo* userInfo, const RtcConnection&amp; connection) = 0;</codeblock>
                <codeblock props="android" outputclass="language-java">public abstract int getUserInfoByUidEx(int uid, UserInfo userInfo, RtcConnection connection);</codeblock>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section id="detailed_desc" deliveryTarget="details" otherprops="no-title">
            <p props="cpp">This method retrieves user information by passing in the user ID. It functions the same as <xref keyref="getUserInfoByUid"/>.</p>
            <p props="android">After a remote user joins a channel, the SDK retrieves the user's ID and user account and caches them in a mapping table. At the same time, it triggers the <xref keyref="onUserInfoUpdated"/> callback on the local client. After receiving this callback, you can call <xref keyref="getUserInfoByUidEx"/> and pass in the user ID to get the user account from the <xref keyref="UserInfo"/> object.</p>
        </section>
        <section id="scenario" deliveryTarget="details">
            <title>Scenario</title>
            <p>Applicable in multi-channel scenarios.</p>
        </section>
        <section id="parameters" deliveryTarget="details" props="android cpp">
            <title>Parameters</title>
            <parml>
                <plentry props="cpp">
                    <pt>uid</pt>
                    <pd>User ID of the remote user.</pd>
                </plentry>
                <plentry props="cpp">
                    <pt>userInfo</pt>
                    <pd>Input and output parameter representing the <xref keyref="UserInfo"/> object for identifying the user. The <xref keyref="UserInfo"/> object passed in when calling this method will return a <xref keyref="UserInfo"/> object containing the User Account and user ID upon success. See <xref keyref="UserInfo"/>.</pd>
                </plentry>
                <plentry props="cpp">
                    <pt>connection</pt>
                    <pd><xref keyref="RtcConnection"/> object. See <xref keyref="RtcConnection"/>.</pd>
                </plentry>
                <plentry props="android">
                    <pt>uid</pt>
                    <pd>User ID.</pd>
                </plentry>
                <plentry props="android">
                    <pt>userInfo</pt>
                    <pd>The object that identifies the user information. See <xref keyref="UserInfo"/>.</pd>
                </plentry>
                <plentry props="android">
                    <pt>connection</pt>
                    <pd>Connection information. See <xref keyref="RtcConnection"/>.</pd>
                </plentry>
            </parml>
        </section>
        <section id="return_values" props="android cpp">
            <title>Return Values</title>
            <p props="cpp">
                <ul>
                    <li>0: Success.</li>
                    <li>&lt; 0: Failure.</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <p props="android">
                <ul>
                    <li>The <xref keyref="UserInfo"/> object, if the method call succeeds.</li>
                    <li><codeph>null</codeph>, if the method call fails.</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </section>
    </refbody>
</reference>